{{neologism|date=November 2017}}

'''Hyper-interactive teaching technology''' or '''H-ITT''' is a form of technology used primarily to interact between the [[student]]s and [[teacher]]s.  Students generally are given an H-ITT [[transmitter]], which is similar to a [[remote control]], which allows them to answer questions in [[Voting|poll]] or [[quiz]] form.

It also means that the interaction between the teacher, the students and among the students is very high. The term is frequently used to denote a constant conversation among the students themselves, and learning with each other, which is not usually the case in a conventional teaching medium.

